725580f-b.title: Queens: 69th Place - Calamus Avenue
725580f-b.text:
(1)
69th Place (right, beyond body of water), south from Calamus
Ave., showing the Sedgewick House (tower thereon), said to have
been built in the 1870'e. It was still standing in 1934.
April 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
(2)
The same, viewed southeastward across fields from point just
socth of alamus Ave. and west of 69th Place, showing the undewweloped
condition of 69th Place (along line of fence).
April 1925.
Eugene L. Armbruster Collection.
MAY BE REPRODUCED.
